Lots of people don't.

623
01:03:53,005 --> 01:03:54,447
Tonight, I want to speak to everyone else.

624
01:03:55,107 --> 01:03:57,409
People who've never supported me, but are thinking about it.

625
01:03:58,009 --> 01:04:00,691
People who used to support me, but aren't sure if they do anymore.

626
01:04:01,051 --> 01:04:03,333
Or people who are just getting to know me for the first time.

627
01:04:04,641 --> 01:04:05,282
I love Medford.

628
01:04:05,782 --> 01:04:08,265
I grew up here, and I can't imagine living anywhere else.

629
01:04:09,166 --> 01:04:13,911
I first ran for office because I'm committed to making our city, my hometown, a better place.

630
01:04:14,812 --> 01:04:21,119
A Medford where people, whether they're 22 or 82, aren't worried they'll get pushed out of their homes because Medford's not affordable anymore.

631
01:04:21,880 --> 01:04:25,285
A city of yes, where we come together and get big things done.

632
01:04:25,945 --> 01:04:34,517
A Medford that is not for sale, where we have a head seat at the negotiating table and we make sure that developers, Tufts, or the MBTA pay their fair share.

633
01:04:35,318 --> 01:04:39,743
A Medford for all of us, where we stand up for our inclusive values and protect our neighbors.

634
01:04:40,845 --> 01:04:47,389
The Facebook bullies have tried to paint a pretty nasty picture of me, but I ask you to ignore the noise and talk to people who actually know me.

635
01:04:48,249 --> 01:04:54,452
I've sat down with hundreds of people who don't agree with me, whether that's about the city budget, or zoning, or street safety.

636
01:04:55,113 --> 01:05:00,096
We've had good conversations, we've learned from each other, and I've made better decisions because of it.

637
01:05:00,976 --> 01:05:04,058
I don't pretend that I have all the answers, and I admit when I'm wrong.

638
01:05:05,145 --> 01:05:09,007
That's who I am, and it's the kind of leadership I want to see in my own representatives.

639
01:05:09,787 --> 01:05:13,848
Whether you vote for me or not, I will continue to listen, learn, and lead with compassion.

640
01:05:14,449 --> 01:05:22,752
I work hard every single day for our city, and win or lose, I'll keep working to help make the best choices we can for Medford's future, because I love living here.

641
01:05:23,472 --> 01:05:29,335
I'm Zach Baers, I'm running for re-election to the Medford City Council, and I hope I can earn your support and your vote on November 4th.

642
01:05:29,695 --> 01:05:29,935
Thank you.

643
01:05:37,099 --> 01:05:38,620
Next we'll hear from Anna Callahan.

644
01:05:45,244 --> 01:05:45,824
Thank you so much.

645
01:05:45,904 --> 01:05:47,085
Thanks everyone for being here.

646
01:05:47,645 --> 01:05:48,726
My name is Anna Callahan.

647
01:05:48,766 --> 01:05:52,128
I'm a first term incumbent and I am running for re-election.

648
01:05:52,848 --> 01:06:02,294
So you can count on me to represent the values that I believe we share here in Medford and that means having

649
01:06:02,994 --> 01:06:23,430
really vibrant community where you can walk to a local shop and run into friends and neighbors along the way and we support each other, an inclusive city where everyone feels welcome, a green and sustainable city, as well as a really vibrant democracy where people are actually engaged in the political process.

650
01:06:24,330 --> 01:06:29,635
A few of my policy positions, I do think that we need to spend more on our roads.

651
01:06:29,695 --> 01:06:32,097
We have some savings that we could be spending on our roads.

652
01:06:32,538 --> 01:06:38,703
And the thing to understand about roads is that the more dilapidated they are, the more expensive they are to repair.

653
01:06:39,023 --> 01:06:48,792
So it's actually financially responsible for us to bring those back up into better shape quickly, because then it'll be easier and cheaper for us to repair going forward.

654
01:06:49,892 --> 01:07:02,820
I know we really have to tackle our housing crisis, and I want us to be creative and think about ways that we can create more affordable housing, keep tenants in their home, keep older folks aging in place.

655
01:07:03,921 --> 01:07:12,606
And, you know, I really want us to have local businesses and to support our small local shops and have vibrant squares.

656
01:07:13,606 --> 01:07:22,451
The thing that makes me truly unique as an elected official is how I engage the community in making our city a better place.

657
01:07:22,951 --> 01:07:26,654
It's how much I care about democracy and engaging people in the political process.

658
01:07:27,234 --> 01:07:34,198
So I have a whole team of volunteers dedicated to helping me set up listening sessions throughout the community.

659
01:07:34,478 --> 01:07:37,960
And out of those listening sessions come policy ideas that people want to work on.

660
01:07:38,360 --> 01:07:45,743
I have five volunteer teams working on different ideas that came up from the community, and I invite you to reach out to me.

661
01:07:45,843 --> 01:07:48,864
I would love to hear your ideas and help you work on them together.

662
01:07:49,264 --> 01:07:49,564
Thank you.

663
01:07:55,166 --> 01:07:57,066
Next, Nick Giuleo.

664
01:08:04,029 --> 01:08:05,129
Perfect pronunciation.

665
01:08:12,768 --> 01:08:17,453
A great teacher I had at the school we're in tonight once told me that you should always end a speech with a thank you for listening.

666
01:08:17,973 --> 01:08:22,838
I'll take his advice but flip the timing and begin by thanking all of you for being here and listening.

667
01:08:24,119 --> 01:08:25,600
Our city might be more divided than ever.

668
01:08:26,421 --> 01:08:32,006
Rather than brood on the reasons why in these two minutes I have with you, I'd like to instead reflect on the path forward.

669
01:08:33,167 --> 01:08:36,288
I have no doubt that everyone on this stage wants what is best for Medford.

670
01:08:36,908 --> 01:08:46,052
We may disagree on what is best and how we get there, but I think the most important thing to remember is that the system of government our city operates under was designed to handle these differences.

671
01:08:47,232 --> 01:08:50,493
Medford is an enormous city, nearly 60,000 people.

672
01:08:51,214 --> 01:08:57,336
There's no doubt that among the 60,000, we have residents with a very wide range of perspectives, ideas, and points of view.

673
01:08:58,493 --> 01:09:02,214
I've always been a strong believer that diversity in this respect makes government better.

674
01:09:02,994 --> 01:09:11,777
It avoids the many pitfalls of groupthink and leads to legislating that, while might not leave no one fully happy, represents workable compromise.

675
01:09:12,658 --> 01:09:15,819
Compromise is good and is something I believe we should all be striving for.

676
01:09:16,979 --> 01:09:26,044
I've said much in these many months of campaigning, but of all the themes I've touched on, the one that has given me the most passion to keep going is the value of the ordinary person's opinion.

677
01:09:27,004 --> 01:09:39,331
My first glimpse of this was in my professional life when I tried my first few cases before a jury, but I really learned it observing the many intelligent people in our community come up to the podium at our meetings and express their thoughts on the issues that matter to them.

678
01:09:40,291 --> 01:09:41,551
We need to preserve that voice.

679
01:09:42,332 --> 01:09:44,352
We need to be wary of a government that discounts it.

680
01:09:45,013 --> 01:09:49,034
The voice of the ordinary person matters, and their collective voice makes a difference.

681
01:09:50,355 --> 01:09:57,857
The greatest case I can make to you for electing me is I have a passion to preserve this voice, and it goes far beyond the voices of people I already agree with.

682
01:09:58,677 --> 01:09:59,998
I want to hear from people who don't.

683
01:10:01,004 --> 01:10:03,886
I want to hear from people whose perspectives differ from my own.

684
01:10:04,847 --> 01:10:10,210
I want to hear from all voices in Medford, because every voice matters, and the city we call home.

685
01:10:10,751 --> 01:10:11,051
Thank you.

686
01:10:13,412 --> 01:10:18,756
I'd like to ask Matt Lemming to come forward.

687
01:10:30,380 --> 01:10:31,801
Everybody, my name is Matt.

688
01:10:32,661 --> 01:10:36,183
I'm a first term city councilor in Medford running for a second term.

689
01:10:37,303 --> 01:10:45,368
When I first moved here, I was a postdoc at Mass General and back then I was barely able to afford a room in a small apartment.

690
01:10:45,408 --> 01:10:53,752
Now that's not because of the fact that my, that's not because my research wasn't important enough to earn

691
01:10:54,777 --> 01:10:56,858
larger housing space.

692
01:10:56,898 --> 01:11:00,300
That's because the housing system we have right now is broken.

693
01:11:00,320 --> 01:11:09,405
In the past four decades, rents have risen over 300 percent, home prices more than 400 percent, and incomes have grown only 37 percent.

694
01:11:10,545 --> 01:11:16,468
That's why I got involved locally, first by lobbying council to create Medford's Affordable Housing Trust, and then running myself in 2023.

695
01:11:19,281 --> 01:11:24,507
Medford faces two big challenges, a strained budget and housing that is far too expensive.

696
01:11:24,968 --> 01:11:28,632
And the city was for too long penny smart and dollar stupid.

697
01:11:29,093 --> 01:11:33,338
And I've been working with my colleagues to bring Medford out of this stagnancy this past term.

698
01:11:34,722 --> 01:11:41,623
This past term, backed by parents and families, we passed a ballot initiative that saved 40 teaching jobs and funded a full-time road repair crew.

699
01:11:41,643 --> 01:11:49,105
And I look forward next term to supporting the building of a new high school, even if it requires a debt exclusion to fund.

700
01:11:49,785 --> 01:11:54,485
We approved new senior housing, and I've been working to fund our new affordable housing trust that I lobbied for.

701
01:11:55,366 --> 01:12:02,647
I worked with the State House on a bill that will update our developer impact fees for the first time in 34 years so that we can upgrade our infrastructure.

702
01:12:03,898 --> 01:12:10,704
We're modernizing our rules around development, making our city's growth greener, more sustainable, and aligned with Medford's long-term vision.

703
01:12:12,170 --> 01:12:21,652
I've pushed for a more transparent city council, starting a newsletter, live-streaming meetings, holding office hours, and writing all of it on my website nonstop.

704
01:12:21,752 --> 01:12:32,294
I launched a program to house low-income veterans and create an emergency fund for in-need veterans, and I proudly championed our Welcoming City Ordinance, which offers protections to vulnerable non-citizen residents.

705
01:12:32,894 --> 01:12:34,974
Local government has stopped kicking the can down the road.

706
01:12:35,054 --> 01:12:37,455
I'm fighting for a more affordable, vibrant Medford.

707
01:12:37,515 --> 01:12:38,475
I'll keep doing that work.

708
01:12:39,356 --> 01:12:40,878
Thank you very much for your time.

709
01:12:40,958 --> 01:12:43,320
I realize that Phyllis is standing right here.

710
01:12:44,782 --> 01:12:47,725
Very last sentence, thank you for your time, and don't forget to vote on November 4th.

711
01:12:51,729 --> 01:12:52,130
Thanks.

712
01:12:52,610 --> 01:12:54,953
I'd like to call Liz Mullay to the podium.

713
01:13:01,705 --> 01:13:06,070
Hi, my name is Liz Mullane and I'm a new candidate running for Medford City Council.

714
01:13:06,770 --> 01:13:18,022
I want to start by thanking the Medford Democratic City Committee for organizing tonight and to my fellow candidates and everyone in attendance here or watching at home for their participation in this process.

715
01:13:19,043 --> 01:13:31,916
I believe that my 20 years of experience working within nonprofits, building programs, raising funds, managing budgets, and leading teams at complex, multilayered organizations would be an asset on the City Council.

716
01:13:32,757 --> 01:13:42,326
As a fundraiser, being able to identify new sources of revenue to fund our community services that benefit everyone, like our libraries, senior centers, and mental health providers.

717
01:13:43,187 --> 01:13:56,233
with my MBA taking a close eye to our budgets for more transparency, addressing a array of shortfalls, and helping to prioritize key areas, like repairing our streets and sidewalks to make them more accessible for all of our residents.

718
01:13:57,727 --> 01:14:12,816
Additionally, this background will allow me to provide guidance in bringing in and keeping more small business in Medford through streamlining our process, providing incentives, and eliminating the barriers of entry into our city, all the while helping to grow our commercial tax base.

719
01:14:13,837 --> 01:14:23,003
As an adjunct faculty member in higher ed, I've seen firsthand just how important it is to fund our schools and advocate for our students to set them up for lifelong success.

720
01:14:24,403 --> 01:14:35,349
I will stand up and continue to stand up for my neighbors against ICE, protect the individual rights of our residents, invest in affordable housing, and champion for sustainability and more green space.

721
01:14:36,550 --> 01:14:43,994
I am a listener, a collaborator, and a person who simply wants to use their knowledge to continue moving Medford forward.

722
01:14:44,534 --> 01:14:51,058
Because I believe when we invest in our community, in our children, our families, and our seniors, we all win.

723
01:14:51,978 --> 01:14:55,660
I hope you'll consider me as one of your seven votes on Tuesday, November 4th.

724
01:14:56,080 --> 01:14:56,401
Thank you.

725
01:15:01,804 --> 01:15:04,105
And I'd like to call Justin to come to the podium.

726
01:15:04,145 --> 01:15:05,126
Justin Tang.

727
01:15:11,850 --> 01:15:13,230
Thank you all for being here tonight.

728
01:15:14,111 --> 01:15:15,832
Folks, Medford is a special place.

729
01:15:16,753 --> 01:15:20,855
My parents moved here over 20 years ago because it was where they could afford to find a home.

730
01:15:22,135 --> 01:15:25,677
Little did they know they were joining a community that would mean so much to them.

731
01:15:26,498 --> 01:15:34,403
As they worked paycheck to paycheck, they could always count on their neighbors to lend a hand, to look after me after school, and to make sure we got by.

732
01:15:35,083 --> 01:15:40,087
And our public schools gave me opportunities I never imagined, including the chance to attend Harvard Law School.

733
01:15:40,928 --> 01:15:51,738
There's something special about Medford that a shy little boy in the back of a classroom who started kindergarten not knowing many words of English could one day find his voice and give back to the city he's always called home.

734
01:15:53,026 --> 01:16:11,878
I ran because I wanted the next generation to have even more opportunities than I did, because too often City Hall felt like a place where you needed to know someone to get something done, because diversity too often felt like just a slogan, and because too many of my friends were being priced out while our schools struggled to get by.

735
01:16:12,438 --> 01:16:14,120
The status quo just wasn't working.

736
01:16:15,020 --> 01:16:32,541
Over my last two terms, we've begun to change that, making historic investments in streets, schools, taking on the housing crisis through once-in-generations reforms that create hundreds of new affordable housing units, and standing up for our neighbors' rights, safety, and financial security.

737
01:16:33,482 --> 01:16:36,444
But in a time like this, Medford can't afford to turn back.

738
01:16:37,045 --> 01:16:40,967
This is our opportunity to dream big and act bravely.

739
01:16:41,568 --> 01:16:49,013
An opportunity to keep building a city that welcomes and listens to everyone, whether you've lived here your whole life or whether you just moved in yesterday.

740
01:16:49,973 --> 01:16:54,877
Our opportunity to rebuild Medford High, invest in our students, and repave our roads.

741
01:16:55,717 --> 01:16:59,959
With steady hands and bold leadership, we can keep building a future for us all.

742
01:17:00,699 --> 01:17:22,367
Two rounds of two-minute answers aren't enough to answer everything and to lay out a comprehensive vision for the city, but I hope you'll visit my website at www.justin4medford.com, the number four, and it's been an honor to speak to you all tonight to serve the city, and I ask for one of your votes on November 4th.

743
01:17:22,587 --> 01:17:23,168
Thank you so much.

744
01:17:29,902 --> 01:17:31,163
I'm just going to take a few minutes.

745
01:17:31,363 --> 01:17:36,144
Of course, we finished ahead of time because we did not have all the candidates for a variety of reasons.

746
01:17:37,225 --> 01:17:48,548
But I do want to take a moment to thank the candidates for being here tonight, for sharing your responses to the questions from the citizens of Medford, for sharing why you want to serve in our great city.

747
01:17:49,008 --> 01:17:53,850
Because I do believe we have a great city, and I'm very happy that we are given opportunities

748
01:17:54,330 --> 01:18:04,595
to have events like this to inform the public and where the public can also have input into what they'd like to find out about people running for positions in our city.

749
01:18:05,055 --> 01:18:19,801
So I'd like to thank, if anyone doesn't mind to indulge me for a moment, I'd like to thank the members of the Democratic Committee, Bruce, Mark, Anne, and Max, because a lot of time and effort went into preparing this night and they were happy to do so.

750
01:18:19,861 --> 01:18:21,562
So I'd like to thank them for doing that.

751
01:18:24,929 --> 01:18:26,951
I want to thank the Tufts volunteers.

752
01:18:26,971 --> 01:18:28,131
I want you to stand up.

753
01:18:28,212 --> 01:18:30,633
It's so nice to see the young people with us.

754
01:18:30,733 --> 01:18:34,396
I think that's a step in the right direction for MedFed.

755
01:18:35,217 --> 01:18:39,820
I want to thank Kevin who came to some of our meetings via Zoom so we could help with the audio.

756
01:18:41,681 --> 01:18:47,503
And I want to thank the audio and visual people, the media, and Medford High School for allowing us to use this facility.

757
01:18:48,063 --> 01:18:50,864
The most important thing I'd like to say this evening is this.

758
01:18:51,664 --> 01:18:55,746
We have a vote coming, and we have that wonderful opportunity.

759
01:18:55,786 --> 01:19:01,648
We have the gift of voting for the people we think will best bring our city forward.

760
01:19:02,128 --> 01:19:05,849
So our voting day is November 4th.

761
01:19:06,469 --> 01:19:07,930
Early voting starts October 25th.

762
01:19:07,970 --> 01:19:08,210
So vote.

763
01:19:11,152 --> 01:19:14,882
if you want to have great representation moving our city forward.

764
01:19:15,163 --> 01:19:16,427
Thank you all for coming tonight.

765
01:19:16,507 --> 01:19:17,670
Thank you to the candidates.

766
01:19:17,750 --> 01:19:18,833
Good luck to all of you.

